            <section class="mt-8 prose prose-sm">
              <h2>How the Michigan income tax calculator works</h2>
              <p>
                Michigan uses a flat state income tax rate, meaning the same
                percentage applies to all taxable income (after deductions and
                exemptions). Many cities in Michigan also levy their own local
                income tax.
              </p>
              <p>This calculator estimates your Michigan liability by:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Converting your income to an annual amount (if you choose
                  monthly or hourly).
                </li>
                <li>Subtracting any pre‑tax deductions you enter.</li>
                <li>
                  Applying the Michigan flat state income tax rate to your
                  taxable income.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Optionally applying a local city income tax rate you provide.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <div class="formula-box">
                <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Formulas used</p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Annual income (hourly)</strong> = hourly wage × hours
                  per week × weeks per year
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Michigan taxable income</strong> = max(0, annual
                  income − pre‑tax deductions)
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>State tax</strong> = Michigan taxable income × state
                  tax rate
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Local city tax</strong> = Michigan taxable income ×
                  local city tax rate
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Total MI tax</strong> = state tax + local city tax
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Effective MI tax rate</strong> = total MI tax ÷ annual
                  income
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Net (after MI tax)</strong> = annual income − total MI
                  tax
                </p>
              </div>

